The constant tinkering ensures there will be new iterations of The Life of Pablo as time progresses, becoming the...
Despite the fact it's one of the most heavily pirated albums of recent memory—partly due to its lack of widespread commercial release.
With indefinite updates and limited commercial release, Kanye West still has SOME form of control with his music.
Why should Kanye West have opted for a more traditional route being cognizant of piracy culture and low album sales?
